Parking areas digitized only in the DMAP Transit and Pedestrian Study Area. 2012 Update: Additional parking locations were added using the 2012 aerial photography with business license data provided by Excise and License.</abstract>       <purpose>The parking garage and surface parking datasets were intended to provide city planners, Public Works management, traffic engineers, and Excise and Licenses with information as to parking capacity, parking rates, parking lot locations, and the business licenses file number.</purpose>       <supplinf>This dataset combines the former Parking Garage and Surface Parking layers.</supplinf>     </descript>     <status>       <update>As needed</update>     </status>     <spdom>       <bounding>         <westbc>-105.036595</westbc>         <eastbc>-104.665166</eastbc>         <northbc>39.852772</northbc>         <southbc>39.62812</southbc>       </bounding>     </spdom>     <keywords>       <theme>         <themekt>None</themekt>         <themekey>parking</themekey>       </theme>       <theme>         <themekt>ISO 19115 Topic Categories</themekt>         <themekey>planningCadastre</themekey>         <themekey>structure</themekey>         <themekey>transportation</themekey>       </theme>       <place>         <placekt>None</placekt>         <placekey>Denver</placekey>         <placekey>Denver County</placekey>         <placekey>Colorado</placekey>         <placekey>USA</placekey>       </place>     </keywords>     <accconst>None</accconst>     <useconst>ACCESS CONSTRAINTS:   None.
